parameters: Cheers. \n< Serena >
Cheers. \n< Erika >
\n< Serena >
...Pwa. \n< Erika >
Haha! So this is what they call the sweet taste of
victory! \n< Erika >
I couldn't even have a sip of alcohol when I was
hospitalized right after the Minotaur incident. \n< Erika >
To redo that celebration now, what a strange person as
always. \n< Serena >
You can really hold your liquor. You must have
learned the taste of alcohol in that town over there. \n< Erika >
Well then, one more drink... \n< Erika >
Lady Erika, considering your condition, it might not
be wise to drink too much. \n< Serena >
Oh, right... Alcohol is bad for your stomach... Or was
it? \n< Erika >
What about that stomach... \n< Serena >
Well, I haven't slept with any other man around that
time. I guess one of them hit the mark. \n< Erika >
I also suffered serious injuries and couldn't have an
abortion. Before I knew it, I ended up with this
belly. \n< Erika >
Well, if it has come to this, then I have no choice
but to give birth. Even if the child was conceived
through rape, I still have to give birth. \n< Erika >
Well, it's fine as far as I'm concerned. \n< Erika >
By the way, you can hold your liquor quite well too.
Have you also learned to appreciate the taste of
alcohol in that town over there? \n< Erika >
Well, I've never thought it was delicious, but now,
maybe just a little.... \n< Serena >
No, it still has a strange taste. It makes my nose
crinkle. \n< Serena >
Tahhahaha. That's fine. Playing around like that since
I was a kid has turned me into a nobody like me who
doesn't amount to much. \n< Erika >
If I could be like Lady Erika, perhaps I should strive
a little harder to enjoy drinking sake. \n< Serena >
Oh, me? Nah, my body's all beaten up and nothing's
going well for me. There's no point in aiming for
anything for someone like me. Really, truly... \n< Erika >
No, that's not true... I respect you. Even now, in
this very moment, my respect for you is renewed. \n< Serena >
Castrum. In that town, I saw a lot of evil. I also
saw how weak people's hearts can be with just a little
bit of kindness. \n< Serena >
That's why I'm surprised now. \n< Serena >
The way Lady Erika carries herself and behaves. Your
strength. Just how tremendous it is. \n< Serena >
I wonder if I can behave like you. From now on... \n< Serena >
\n< Erika >
Splendor got lost, right? \n< Erika >
Ah, I found it. It was a bit of a struggle. While I'm
here, I'm being taken care of by Lord Merry. \n< Serena >
I'm unharmed and uninjured. I'm really glad...
truly... \n< Serena >
Well, this is the happy ending we were looking for.
Everything is resolved now. \n< Erika >
Well, I don't know. It depends on what father, mother,
and sister say... \n< Serena >
I'm only worried about what kind of moxibustion I'll
receive next. \n< Serena >
Hey hey, squeeze out all the thick flavors and come
here. \n< Erika >
Oh, it's really good. I was worried every day while
lying on the bed. \n< Erika >
I'm so glad nothing happened... \n< Erika >
I-I'm about to cry.... \n< Serena >
No, listen Serena. You don't understand. You don't
understand how much you worry. \n< Erika >
I wonder how Serena is doing now, if she's able to eat
and find a place to stay, if she's not being deceived
by some bad guy, or if she's not getting involved in
something bad... \n< Erika >
I'm lying in a hospital bed. That kind of scene keeps
popping up in my head, disappearing, then appearing
again, and every time it does, it feels like my chest
is tightening. \n< Erika >
Even I am like this, you know. When I consider how
their parents must feel, it's just... My heart aches
for her, you know, like it's pounding so hard. \n< Erika >
Hmm... \n< Serena >
So you better come here ready to be scolded. It's
Serena's duty and responsibility. That's it. \n< Erika >
Hmm... \n< Serena >
...It's a fortunate thing to have a family who worries
about you. I grew up in an orphanage and I've never
seen my parents' faces. \n< Erika >
Is that so? I remember you ran away from home
before. \n< Serena >
Did I say something like that? You remember it well. \n< Erika >
Well, running away from home means that I came out of
the orphanage. Becoming a nun was never in my plans,
you know. \n< Erika >
Come to think of it, I think I was planning to search
for my mom at first. Even if I had a lead, the only
thing I knew was her hair color. \n< Erika >
Speaking of which. \n< Serena >
I'm totally devouring it. It's okay though. \n< Erika >
Well, when I was abandoned at the orphanage, my mother
gave me a talisman. It seems like she wanted me to
keep it with me. \n< Erika >
It's woven with hair. I think it's probably Mom's
hair. \n< Erika >
I wonder what kind of person they were, with a
slightly stronger reddish hue than me... Like a wine
red, I guess... \n< Erika >
Hmm? \n< Erika >
An adventurer, huh? I thought I had put up the
'closed' sign for a break... It's always something,
isn't it? \n< Serena >
There is also a possibility that the master forgot his
keys. \n< Erika >
Well, can't be helped... \n< Serena >
Hello there. Yo...! \n< Erika >
No, Lady Erika, please have a seat. I will take care
of this. \n< Serena >
Even Serena is troubled by this. \n< Erika >
Oh... is that so? Sorry, I appreciate it. \n< Erika >

I'm sorry... I've always been a bit clumsy, or maybe

\n< Serena >
Um... Uh, well, um... \n< ??? >

\n< Erika >

is visible from the outside... But on the inside, it's
equally bad. \n< Serena >

\n< Erika >

Ah, I found it. It was a bit of a struggle. While I'm
here, I'm being taken care of by Lord Merry. \n< Serena >
I managed to make it here from the eastern town, but
it seems that being with me right now is quite a
burden for Splendor. \n< Serena >
My lady Merry... If I am near her daughter, Splendor
can also find peace. \n< Serena >
This belly of mine. When I showed my face, they
cried... and were surprised. \n< Serena >
What are you planning to do from now on? \n< Erika >
I am waiting here for a pickup from Grazia. As I have
sent a letter, she will come soon. \n< Serena >
But, it became a serious matter... There were too many
things... \n< Serena >
Even Castrum is in a state of chaos now. I ran away
from there... But what I did while I was there, what
happened because of me... \n< Serena >
Depending on the situation, it could become a problem.
At the very least, Father will likely be implicated. \n< Serena >
If we could be admitted to some monastery or other
before the problem surfaces, we could consider things
settled once and for all. \n< Serena >
It will become an additional burden on my elder
sister. \n< Serena >
Is that okay with Serena? \n< Erika >
Did Serena risk and sacrifice her entire future for
this? Is the end result a life of confinement in a
monastery? \n< Erika >
After going to such lengths to help Spendor, we won't
be able to get along again, right? \n< Erika >
I can't accept this. \n< Erika >
Yeah... I suppose so... \n< Serena >
It didn't necessarily end up as we hoped for... \n< Serena >
I understand... No, wait... \n< Serena >
Hey, let's run away now! It'll be fine! We're probably
just going to be thrown into the monastery anyway,
right!? \n< Erika >
Then why don't you come with me and become an
adventurer instead of dealing with the hassle of that
stupid house! ... Yeah! Let's become adventurers
together! \n< Erika >
There may be plenty of hardships, but you know what?
At the end of the day, it's all about freedom! The
good and the bad, it's all mine! \n< Erika >
I might feel like, 'What's the point of having a body
like this?' But at least adventurers are free!
Everything, both the happy and the sad, belongs to
oneself! \n< Erika >
My life is mine, right? You don't need to hesitate! \n< Erika >
\n< Serena >
...Honestly, you are so selfish and pushy...
\n< Serena >
And she is a gentle and sincere person. \n< Serena >
You've been considerate of me since the very first
time you spoke to me until now. \n< Serena >
But it's no use. I am a noble. I am an executor of
justice and responsibility. \n< Serena >
... To save Splendor, I sacrificed many things that I
possessed. \n< Serena >
Every time I lose something, I realize how big and
heavy it is. Can such a big thing really come from
within me? \n< Serena >
I thought to myself. It was just as Lady Erika said.
It was just as I heard from Lady Merry. \n< Serena >
I wasn't just built on my parents' love and affection,
but on the love and kindness of many more people, and
even more than that. \n< Serena >
How much time and effort have been spent to shape me
into who I am now. \n< Serena >
How much love has been poured into me? \n< Serena >
I, myself, damaged myself with my selfishness. \n< Serena >
I must return my love to the people I love. I have
selfishly squandered it. \n< Serena >
I must accept that punishment. Running away from
responsibility and guilt would only make me the same
as many of the adults who have tormented me. \n< Serena >
That is just unbearable... \n< Serena >
Wait, Serena, that conclusion is wrong. Why did you
think that way? \n< Erika >
No one wants that kind of thing from you. That kind of
thing... \n< Erika >
What I want for myself. \n< Serena >
As I looked at Lady Erika, I thought that once again. \n< Serena >
You surely did not run away from your responsibility. \n< Serena >
The pain and toil of those consequences. You carry it
all without uttering a single complaint to me. \n< Serena >
Everything that comes out of their mouth are words of
concern for me...I was impressed. I thought there was
such a strong person. \n< Serena >
I have the same pain now, and that's why I feel
strongly. I want to be like you too. \n< Serena >
No, no. That's not me... I am... \n< Erika >
Thank you, Lady Erika. Thanks to you, my heart feels
brighter than ever before. \n< Serena >

I will write a letter. \n< Serena >
I may write about the mundane things I think about or
read on a daily basis, and the content may be
uninteresting. \n< Serena >
I would be happy if you could read it. \n< Serena >
I'll go outside and take a breath of fresh air for a
bit. \n< Serena >
I shall never come to this town again. Look carefully,
remember it well. \n< Serena >
